      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some economic models suggest free trade is optimal, the reality is that the benefits of tariffs are often strategically targeted to correct what are perceived as unfair trade practices. Supporters of tariffs argue that a degree of protection is necessary to nurture nascent domestic industries that cannot compete globally yet. Furthermore, the long-term economic health of a nation depends on a balance between global engagement and the security of its core industries.",
      "source": "target",
