      "content": "that seems like a bit of a stretch though. if you look at history, every time a country leans into protectionism it usually leads to trade wars and higher inflation. isn't it more accurate to say that \"strategic targeting\" is just a fancy way of legitimizing bad economic policy that hurts most people?",
